Simplifying the numerator, we get $\dfrac{\left(\dfrac{1}{11} - \dfrac{1}{3}\right)}{(3 - 11)} = \dfrac{\left(\dfrac{3 - 11}{33}\right)}{-8} = \dfrac{-8}{33(-8)} = \boxed{\dfrac{1}{33}}$.
Final Answer: $\boxed{\dfrac{1}{33}}$. I hope it is correct.
